  "description": "The black hole information paradox is the unresolved conflict between quantum mechanics -- which requires that information is conserved (unitarity) -- and the apparent destruction of information when a [black hole](./black-hole.md) evaporates via [Hawking radiation](./hawking-radiation.md).",
  "name": "Black Hole Information Paradox",
